Patton Oswalt
The always funny (and huggable) standup and comic actor tells a few stories, like the true one about dating a stripper (many years ago). This is part of the well-reviewed essay he wrote as a contributor to the hilarious bestselling book "Things I've Learned From Women Who've Dumped Me" compiled by Ben Karlin (The Daily Show, The Colbert Report, The Onion). A veteran of the King Of Queens sitcom, Oswalt nowadays is a regular on the TV series The United States of Tara and will be making an appearance on the new sci-fi adventure show Dollhouse.

M83
The very atmospheric, some think in the shoegazing style, French electro duo performs "Graveyard Girl" from their latest album, Saturdays = Youth.
